{
  "texts": [
    "In general, node sampling methods exhibit higher efficiency and adaptability in dealing with large-scale graph data compared to node clustering methods.",
    "Therefore, node sampling methods are more suitable for dealing with large-scale datasets.",
    "However, despite their significant advantages, node sampling methods still face challenges such as information loss in practical applications.",
    "These methods simplify the graph structure by selecting representative nodes, which may overlook some important information in the original graph, thus affecting the performance of downstream tasks.",
    "Therefore, when adopting node sampling methods, it is necessary to weigh the balance between efficiency and information integrity and seek further optimization strategies to reduce information loss."
  ]
}